    "longBusinessSummary": "Tracodi Construction Holdings Joint Stock Company engages in the infrastructure construction, quarrying, trading of manufactured and agricultural products, and labor export businesses in Vietnam and internationally. It undertakes projects comprising civil, solar rooftop, windparks, solar farms, and transportation infrastructure. The company is also involved in the mining and processing of construction stones; backfilling, construction, infrastructure, and toll collection; and provides saline, polluted, waste, and daily water treatment services, as well as taxi services. The company was formerly known as Transport and Industry Development Investment Joint Stock Company and changed its name to Transport and Industry Development Investment Joint Stock Company in September 2024. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam. Tracodi Construction Holdings Joint Stock Company is a subsidiary of Bamboo Capital Group.",
